  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The implications can be widespread due to the vast scale and rapidly growing prevalence of AI systems.",
    "Of particular concern is the potential effect of biased AIs on children 67, who have more flexible and malleable knowledge representations and thus may adopt AI systems' biases more readily.",
    "It is important to clarify that our findings do not suggest that all AI systems are biased, nor that all AI-human interactions will create a bias.",
    "To the contrary, we demonstrate that when humans interact with an accurate AI, their judgements become more accurate (consistent with studies showing that human-AI interaction can improve performance outcomes 68).",
    "Rather, the results suggest that when a bias exists in the system it has the potential to amplify via a feedback loop."
  ],
